<br>
Level 24 pet spells, research only?  <br>
Level 29 pet spells, research only?  <br>
They're not sold in OOT that's up to 20 only.  How about the PoK or Katta?<br>
<br>
Do level 20 pets dual wield if I give them two weapons, or is that a level 24 thing?<br>
<br>
Is it worth it to chain summon at this level, or go all out with equipping the pet instead?<br>
<br>
Necro pets get kick and dual at 20/24, how do mage pets compare dmg and hp wise?  How about in the 30s?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
<br>
Onidar, level 20 mage <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://users.rcn.com/mmacauley/blogger.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users.rcn.com/mmacauley/bluewaywreth.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffsterinsf>jeffsterinsf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1860.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: various questions, I'd appreciate any help you can!</span><hr size=1> In retrospect, the best answer is &quot;level faster&quot; -- seriously -- the 20s and 30s forced me to learn the different pets, and become better at using them along the way. Each time you get new pets along the way, you usually get one pair or the other. My notes from back then seem to indicate purchasable spells are:<br>
<br>
24 E<br>
29 AF<br>
34 EW<br>
39 AFW<br>
44 AEFW<br>
49 E<br>
<br>
Katta, as I recall does not have the 39 Earth -- your first HG killer and the only pet that I would deal with researching up until the 49 pets. Katta has, as I recall, one 39 pet not available elsewhere (3 total), and all the 44 pets -- making 49 combines only a single-step process (49 Water would otherwise be a three-step combine.)<br>
<br>
Other spells worth researching are Cornucopia and Everfont. You'll use those a LOT up until you get Gift of Xev at 51. Summon Shard of the Core is, SFAIK, drop only, and have never used it. The rest, including Ring of Flight, Coldstone, the weapons, armor, and bags, Tiny Companion, MS1, etc., were, as I remember purchasable. MS1 is in Iceclad in a gnome igloo, Expedience in the WC tunnel. Rest were PoK, Felwithe, Shadowhaven, or Erudin for me. Oh - Elemental Maelstrom is 5 or 10 pp in the Bazaar. Don't remember where I got Mod Rod -- Mrods are whimpy compared to Trods and have never saved me, though I have one with me at all times.<br>
<br>
49 pets ROCK -- 49 Fire eats two or three HGs for lunch and asks for dessert.  Chews through 400 Kobolds per hour in the Warrens to get your Paineel faction up.  49 Water can handle the WW side of Kael solo. 49 Earth loves Seafurbies, even Quag. 49 Air is a great tank for grouping, especially with stun.<br>
<br>
Pet dual-wielding wasn't at all predictable to me, so hard to say what level two weapons, or what kind work.  Contrary to older posts, level 44 pets are the first that reliably dual-wield without weapons.<br>
<br>
Your choice on equip vs. chain. These days I equip if going after casters to get the pet's MR higher -- two Dagger of Symbols and an Elemental Blanket. If I'm equipping, I throw Fluffy a set of Phantom Plate as well, definitely helps. Still haven't confirmed if handing Fluffy the pieces or the whole bag makes a difference. Sometimes I get generous and give a Gallenite's Bracelet - remember that Phantom armor sets include wrist and there is no way to tell which gets equipped - no hard evidence that Fluffy hits harder with DDs with Bracelet.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps - even with four levels between new spells, you probably get them faster than those at 51 or higher and new spells every level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1860.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: various questions, I'd appreciate any help you can!</span><hr size=1> Thats a lot of questions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Level 24 pet spells, research only? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Some.  Earth can be bought at any mage guild, and I remember having my DE mule buy my Air pet in Neriak.  Water and Fire must be researched.  Not sold in Katta, and not sold in PoK.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Level 29 pet spells, research only? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Again, some.  Air and Fire can be bought.  Water must be *chain* researched at this point, because you need the lvl 24 scroll to make it.  Earth must be researched.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Do level 20 pets dual wield if I give them two weapons, or is that a level 24 thing?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That is a level 24 thing.  Its in the FAQ in the pet forum.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Is it worth it to chain summon at this level, or go all out with equipping the pet instead?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Depends on your style.  I personally play pet cleric, so I often deck my pet out in full armor, swords, rings, blanket, etc.  It is not very mana-efficient, I know, but I find it safer and faster.  I can nuke at will because I won't have to worry about the time it will take the new pet to gain aggro and the 10 seconds I would last in combat.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Necro pets get kick and dual at 20/24, how do mage pets compare dmg and hp wise? How about in the 30s?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
